				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Any one think the Epic 1.5 is kinda weak?<a name="66314"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 11 04 3:57 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The epic 1.5 is a great sword.  The problem is the quest, not the reward.  Bards in guilds that will have a reasonable time at this quest are most likely Time geared.  So let's look at what the upwardly mobile Time bard is going to be toting around.
<br />

<br />
Saryn Shoulders - wind - 2.2
<br />
Edge of Eternity - Percussion - 2.5
<br />
Quarm Bracer - String - 2.4
<br />
Eye of Dreams - Brass 2.2 OR Riz BP - Brass 2.5
<br />
Songblade - voice 2.5 OR Visor of the Berserker - voice 2.2.
<br />

<br />
So the instrument mod on 1.5 is either equal to or less than the mods already on a bard that can get the weapon in a reasonable amount of time.
<br />

<br />
The short duration and long recast of the clicky on the sword means that bards with both EoE/SBotE or EoE/BoAA or EoE/Ethereal Destroyer will be carrying the 1.5 around with 'em for a burst damage clicky and not even equipping the thing for the most part.
<br />

<br />
The 1.5 is a massive upgrade for the bards who won't easily acquire one.  I suppose there's the Elemental but non-Time bards that will see it as a huge upgrade, provided they're in a guild that's willing to do the big fights, but that's a very small number.
<br />

<br />
Overall, it's shameful.  Like our silly lvl 70 title and the pitiful excuse for new songs, SOE has put no real thought into Bards in OoW.
<br />

<br />
I'm very close to getting my 1.5 and I will swing it, but I feel bad for the majority of bards that will never see this thing.
<br />

<br />
Dlandridel Cadence
<br />
Bard of Grey Hawke
<br />
Karana Server
<br />

