				<td colspan="2"><span>Let me start off by saying that unless I sell my bard, Shpiffey will never see epic 1.5 much less 2.0.  I am not currently in a guild because I can never be online much more than 3 hrs at a time.  So basically raiding for me is out.  I have OoW, and will probably be able to make lvl 70 and earn all songs up to lvl 68 and maybe some choice item upgrades.  That is the point where I will hit the ceiling of my progression in EQ.
<br />

<br />
That being said, I wanted to ask a question regarding epic 1.5 based on what I have read so far.  If I were to sum things up, to me, epic 1.5 looks like it has been attained by those bards predominantly in Time+ guilds.  Is that correct?  Of those bards, how many will actually use the thing?  I would think the majority already have better mods and weap combos.  As stated above, the click does not seem very worthwhile.  So what other reason is there to attain 1.5, besides as a &quot;trophy&quot; or because it may be used to attain 2.0?  What about those pre-Time bards out there?  How many of those have 1.5 already?  What about pre-Elemental bards?  If any of these level bards actually have been able to get your epic 1.5, please post how difficult it was for you AND your guild.
<br />

<br />
On a side note, I have a wierd feeling that the more content SoE releases that requires bigger and better equiped raids, the more &quot;casual&quot; players will be weeded out and with it many very skilled players.  By casual I mean players with 4/3/2 groups of dedicated EP/Time/Gates equiped friends or less.  Sorry if this seems like a whine to you, but it is a feeling I just can't seem to shake.  Of course, reading and experiencing the current state of the bard is not helping.</span></td>
